MOORE COUNTY: Weymouth Woods Sandhills Nature 
Preserve, Gum Swamp Trail. Elev. 124 m. Very dry 
habitat, sandhill bordering swamp. Co-occurring species 
include grasses, beech, oak, and *Oxydendrum arboreum*. 
No flowers. Leaves have large divides, seem almost lobed. 
Large patch, with new and old leaves. Roots extensive.
